                <head>222. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On June 18, 1962, Director of the Bureau of Intelligence and Research <persName
                        corresp="#p_HRJ1">Hilsman</persName> transmitted RFE-27 to Assistant
                    Secretary of State for Far Eastern Affairs <persName corresp="#p_HWA2"
                        >Harriman</persName>. This was a progress report summarizing the major goals
                    and accomplishments of the counter-insurgency program in South Vietnam. For text
                    of this memorandum, see <hi rend="italic">United States-Vietnam Relations,
                        1945-1967</hi>, Book 12, pages 469-480.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
